{
  "doc_id": "13750",
  "text": "The points on the fixed point set S ⊂ M of the action obtained by qFK are not triholomorphic. In [CITATION_1] it is shown that the twistor space of any quaternionic manifold with such an S 1 -action can be obtained locally in this way: the fixed point set corresponds on the twistor space Z to a submanifold of complex dimension n with two components on which the corresponding C * -action has constant single weight equal to 1 and one can deduce that Z is of the form as in the quaternionic Feix-Kaledin construction.",
